biweekly.util.com.google.ical.iter

Interface RecurrenceIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterator<DateValue>

    public interface RecurrenceIterator
extends Iterator<DateValue>
    Iterates over a series of dates in a recurrence rule in ascending order.
    Author:
    mikesamuel+svn@gmail.com (Mike Samuel), Michael Angstadt

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void advanceTo(DateValue newStartUtc)
      Skips all dates in the series that come before the given date, so that the next call to next() will return a date on or after the given date (assuming the recurrence includes such a date).
      boolean hasNext()
      Determines if there are more dates in the series.
      DateValue next()
      Returns the next date in the series.
      void remove()
